result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Transcript SENTENCING HEARING commencing JUNE 4, 2015, received and filed.  Original transcript in case file 14CM4865 (36 Pages).

Defendant Demetrius K Holmes in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Owen M. Piotrowski appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case set for Plea & Sentencing. Parties have reached  a resolution in this matter.
AS TO COUNT 1
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on a motion of the state the court ordered Count 1 Dismissed, But Read In to cases 14CM4865 & 15CM471.

Attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub in court, defendant Demetrius K Holmes not in court, in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin. CMC. Defendant's appearance waived. Defense has received discovery and an offer. Bail motion by defense argued and denied by the Court. Defendant enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND. Defense also requests a Plea and Sentencing date. Court granted defense request. Per Judge, Jury Trial set on 6/29/2015. Case adjourned to branch 23.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 4, 2015 at 08:30 am.  Jury trial scheduled for June 29, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with A.S.

Court orders defendant TURNED OVER to JUSTICE Point for Supervision. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.  Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.  Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Demetrius K Holmes in court with attorney Christian Thomas Eichenlaub.  Defendant Demetrius K Holmes in custody.  Carole Manchester appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Grady, Branch 23.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant plead not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for May 22, 2015 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
